# Creating a Function

Use the **def** keyword.

Syntax

```python
def function_name():
    # code
```

---

# Example

```python
def greet():
    print("Hello!")

greet()
```

Output

```
Hello!
```

---

# Calling a Function

A function does nothing until it is called.

```python
def greet():
    print("Hello!")

greet()
greet()
greet()
```

Output

```
Hello!
Hello!
Hello!
```

---

# 🌍 Real-Life Example

Think of a TV Remote.

Press

```
Power Button

↓

TV Turns ON
```

You can press it anytime.

Functions work the same way.

